    <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock screensteps-wrapper--introduction screensteps-wrapper">
  <div id="text-content_3C8C6140-1D6F-0135-0DD0-22000B5A851D" class="text-block-content">
    <p>As an admin, you can enable Open Registration for your entire account. Open registration allows instructors with the appropriate permissions to add users to a course, even if the users don't already have Canvas accounts. When an instructor adds a user to a course, the user is sent a course invitation. To join the course, the user must first register with Canvas and create a password. The user's account will then display in the account Users list.</p>
<p>Even if Open Registration is disabled, admin roles with permission to add or remove users can always add users to courses without Canvas accounts.</p>
<p>Once this feature is enabled, instructors can add users in the course People page.</p>
  </div>
</div>

